{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a10edb6b-5cbd-46f1-af98-a0efd3a42441","content":"MSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` files. The replacement is a `.runsettings` file. I've created `local.runsettings` that migrates your two settings:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `AssemblyResolution` / `useLoadContext` | `<MSTest><AssemblyResolution>` |\n| `TestTimeout` (30 000 ms) | `<RunConfiguration><TestSessionTimeout>` |\n\n**To wire it up**, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**For per-test timeouts** (instead of session-wide), you can also use the `[Timeout(30000)]` attribute on individual test methods or a base class.\n\nYou can safely delete `local.testsettings` once you've verified tests run correctly with the new file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f5cddb0a-3529-4128-b120-3529ea97c83d","outputTokens":250},"id":"e24fc50c-6710-44c7-8bd7-01752fc58ace","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:02:03.700Z","parentId":"de9112b6-04b1-4287-b982-125c6e07b15e"}
